<div class="help-content-wrap"><h3 id="dice-battle">Dice Battle</h3>
<h4 id="red-vs-blue-betting-area">RED VS. BLUE BETTING AREA</h4>
<p><img src="../../../../assets/dicebattle-1.png" alt=""></p>
<h4 id="profit-introduction">PROFIT INTRODUCTION</h4>
<p>&quot;Red&quot; (red side) and &quot;Blue&quot; (blue side) each hold 3 dice.
The winner is the one with the highest sum of the points on the dice thrown by the two of them. The &quot;Red&quot; and &quot;Blue&quot; will then compete in the betting area and customers can only between the &quot;Red&quot; or the &quot;Blue&quot; to place their bets. Bets are paid in proportion of the amount placed as bets.</p>
<h4 id="cash-return">CASH RETURN</h4>
<p>1) If no bets were placed on the Red (side) or the Blue (side), the entire sum of cash placed as bets will be returned to the customers after the results are displayed;
2) If the Red and the Blue’s game ends as a tie, the entire sum of cash placed as bets will be returned to the customers after the results are displayed;
3)  If the total number of placed bets on both sides (Red and Blue) are not the same, then, the side which had the least amount placed as bets will have that amount entering the Prize Pot. In the end, the customers who bet on the side which loses, will see the amount they placed as bets enter the &quot;Prize Pot&quot; which will be won and distributed among the winning side. The winning side will then share the winnings in proportion to the betting amount that customers placed as bets.</p>
<h4 id="playing-specific-dice-points-in-the-betting-area">PLAYING SPECIFIC DICE POINTS IN THE BETTING AREA</h4>
<p><img src="../../../../assets/dicebattle-2.png" alt=""></p>
<p>Customers can also bet on specific points (numbers) of the dice; customers will also be rewarded if their selected numbers are correct.</p>
<p>Pair (2.3x): 2 out of the 3 thrown dice have the same number of dice points.
Straight (8x): the 3 thrown dice have numbers of dice points that form a sequence of numbers (e.g. 1, 2, 3; 2, 3, 4; 3, 4, 5; or 4, 5, 6).
Triple (30x): the 3 thrown dice have the exact same number of dice points in each of the dice.</p>
<p><img src="../../../../assets/dicebattle-3.png" alt=""></p>
